{
  "_meta": {
    "name": "Endurance Retail Door Designer - full option catalogue (enquiry-only)",
    "source": "bmapprocaldoorportalretail.azurewebsites.net/Default.aspx",
    "captured": "2026-06-25 (live, via client-side mJobState)",
    "BIG_FINDING": "The ENTIRE catalogue is held client-side in window.mJobState.Job.Options - an array of option fields, each with Heading, CurrentOption, and SubOptions[] where every choice has {Description (label), ID (Endurance's internal id), ImageURL, Images}. This means the configurator's data backbone (labels, IDs AND door render images) can be GENERATED PROGRAMMATICALLY rather than hand-built, and the catalogue-sync (drift detection) is trivial: re-read mJobState and diff. Field order/indices differ per door type - map by Heading, not index.",
    "extractionRecipe": "For each door type (select it in the UI), read window.mJobState.Job.Options; for per-style glazing, select each Door Design and read the 'Door Glass' field. Each SubOption.ID + ImageURL gives you the asset + identifier per choice.",
    "status": "Comprehensive. Lists captured directly from data. Per-style glazing captured as representative samples (full per-style mapping is one scripted pass via the recipe above).",
    "extractorScript": "endurance-catalogue-extractor.js \u2014 paste into the designer's browser console (logged in) and run EXT.captureAllTypes() then EXT.download(). Produces the COMPLETE tree for all 4 types with option IDs, image URLs, and the per-style glazing matrix, as a downloadable JSON. Re-run any time to sync against catalogue drift.",
    "imageData": "Each choice's render images are at SubOption.Images[n].ImageURL (and OnRightImageURL for double doors), with layout geometry (CX, CY, W, H, Rotation, FlipH). The extractor captures these. Image URLs can't be transcribed here but download with the script.",
    "optionIDs": "Every choice has an Endurance internal numeric ID (SubOption.ID) and each field a Category number; SelectOption(category, id) sets it. The extractor captures all IDs \u2014 these are what a build would map selections to.",
    "avantalDifferences": "Avantal (aluminium range) differs structurally: NO internal colour, NO knocker, NO spyhole / security chain / separate Lock field, and NO 'Door Hinged On' (uses Master Leaf instead). Frame Colour limited to 3. 13 style\u00d7cassette combos, 5 external colours, 4 hinges, 25 handles."
  },
